         <abstract>
            <p>Taxes must be so devised as to encourage capital investment and industrial expansion. Recommendations by business include repeal of renegotiation, termination of excess profits tax at war's end, postwar reserves, no increases in income tax, integration of Victory tax and other taxes, excess profits credit of 100% of average earnings, extending relief provisions of sec. 722 to changes in character of business occurring after base period, extending time for qualification of pension trusts, extending tax benefit rule to depreciation, eliminating penalty tax for consolidated returns, eliminating intercorporate dividend tax and double taxation of corporate earnings, repeal of capital stock and declared value excess profits taxes, and adoption of retail sales tax.</p>
